To test whether the late-layer adapter-delta signals causally mediate final safe-action margins, we patched final-token residual-stream states between Base and each adapter. For adapter A, A-to-Base patching measures whether adapter states are sufficient to move the Base model toward the adapter, while Base-to-A patching measures whether replacing adapter states with Base states removes the adapter effect. We report recovered and removed fractions of the clean adapter margin shift across layers.
